observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the management instruct the Municipal Accounting Office to:
Establish a system and control procedures in accounting for infrastructure project especially that the LGU prefers to implement them by administration, which requires thorough monitoring; 
Maintain a subsidiary record on a per project basis, since some of the individual projects were merged against previously completed projects;
Draw up adjusting entries to recognize the noted undervalued projects and capital expenditures which were erroneously recognized as expense;
Draw up a JEV to correct the subsidiary records on the noted mis-postings;
Prepare correct subsidiary ledgers relative to the Muli- Purpose Buildings constructed in nine barangays which were lumped under two SLs; and
Coordinate with the Municipal Engineer’s Office for proper monitoring and recording of expenditures of infrastructure projects.

Recommendation/s:
We reiterated our recommendations to the Head of the Agency to require the Accounting Office to:
Continue exhausting all means necessary to obtain the needed reports, records and documents to identify the variances from the period 2013 and below and make the adjusting entries, as warranted;
Reconcile the items recorded in the accounts in CY 2014 and above and effect the necessary adjustments;
Submit to the Office of the Auditor the reconciliation papers and journal entry voucher for the adjustments, for audit and verification; and
Henceforth, ensure due diligence in the recording of reciprocal accounts and conduct regular reconciliation of the accounts to timely address any variances.

Recommendation/s:
We reiterated our recommendation the management to instruct the Municipal Accounting Office to:
Issue demand letters to the identified LGU/BGUs and submit to the audit team a copy of said demand letters;
Expedite the evaluation of collectability of the receivable accounts and exert more efforts in the retrieval of supporting documents;
Initiate the processing of the request for authority to write-off the accounts which are uncertain for collection due to being dormant for more than 10 years in accordance with the guidelines and procedures set forth in COA Circular No. 2016-005; and
Closely monitor and follow up the barangays on the timely submission of liquidation reports on outstanding fund transfers.

Recommendation/s:
We recommended to the management to undertake the following:
Require the Inventory Committee to properly fill up the RPCI following the instruction set by the existing circular;
Instruct the Inventory Committee to prepare and submit the remaining RPCI for items physically counted as of December 3, 2024 and thereafter submit altogether the report of physical count conducted;
Require the Inventory Committee to include all inventories, particularly the accountable forms and donated or transferred drugs and medicines, and vaccines from other NGAs in the conduct of physical count and the preparation and submission of RPCI;
Require the concerned office of the LGU to furnish the accounting office a copy of the document pertaining to receipt of supplies donated or transferred by other government agencies or private entities for proper recording in the books of accounts;
Require the accounting office to record purchases of accountable forms thru the inventory account and issuances thereof shall be recorded as they take place;
emind the accounting personnel tasked with the preparation of Journal Entry Vouchers
to use the proper account title appropriate to the transaction and to personnel assigned to
review the accounting entry during approval of the JEV
