We recommended that management require the following:
For Small Value Procurements, the BAC Secretariat shall ensure that the terms and conditions be indicated in the face of the Purchase Order and make sure that it was properly acknowledged and dated by the supplier. For procurement through competitive bidding, the BAC Secretariat shall attach to the DV the duly received and dated Notice to Proceed (NTP) and Contract Agreement, showing the delivery terms and conditions;
The GSO personnel in charge with the receipt and acceptance of delivered goods shall require from the supplier, upon delivery, the delivery receipts with complete details as to quantity and description. The DRs shall be signed and dated based on the actual delivery date. These shall be attached to the Disbursement Voucher together with the charge invoices;
The Municipal Accountant or any accounting personnel tasked to check the completeness of the supporting documents to the DV shall ensure (a) that complete Delivery Receipts were attached, signed and dated, (b) completeness of the terms and conditions and presence of the supplier’s signature with date, in the Purchase Order, (c) that the IAR duly signed by the Acceptor and Inspector of goods are dated and (d) that the Notice to Proceed and Contract Agreement, for goods procured through competitive bidding, are attached to identify whether deliveries were made on time or with delay. Any deviation or delay noted in the deliveries shall be meticulously checked to enable withholding of liquidated damages, if warranted.

